
Solana is a blockchain platform which uses a proof-of-stake mechanism to provide smart contract functionality.   
Its native cryptocurrency is SOL.
Solana blockchain uses the Rust programming language for developing smart contracts, referred to as programs.

Hellow World!!!
```
// declare and export the program's entrypoint
entrypoint!(process_instruction);
 
// program entrypoint's implementation
pub fn process_instruction(
    program_id: &Pubkey,
    accounts: &[AccountInfo],
    instruction_data: &[u8]
) -> ProgramResult {
    // print statement
    msg!("Hello, world!");
 
    // gracefully exit the program
    Ok(())
}
```
